    public class NestedInvalidationListenerBuilder.Buildable
extends NestedInvalidationListenerBuilder
    A subtype of NestedInvalidationListenerBuilder which can actually build a listener with buildAttached().

    • Method Detail

      • buildAttached

        public NestedInvalidationListenerHandle buildAttached()
        Builds and attaches a nested invalidation listener and returns the handle for it.

        This method can only be called once as the same InvalidationListener should not be added more than once to the same Nesting.

        Returns:
        a new instance of NestedInvalidationListenerHandle; initially attached
        See Also:
        buildDetached()

      • buildDetached

        public NestedInvalidationListenerHandle buildDetached()
        Builds a nested invalidation listener and returns the handle for it.

        Note that the listener is not yet attached!

        This method can only be called once as the same InvalidationListener should not be added more than once to the same Nesting.

        Returns:
        a new instance of NestedInvalidationListenerHandle; initially detached
        See Also:
        buildAttached()
